snippet.textDisplay: "This song is produced by a well-known and genius producer belonging to Coke Studio. The song was uploaded to the internet on April 14, 2024, as the first episode of Coke Studio Season 15. This song represents the Thar-Rajhistan Sindhi culture (Sindh and Sindhi culture are among the oldest civilizations, named the Civilization of the Indus Valley, and Mohenjo-Daro is the living proof of this civilization. Nowadays, Sindh is located in Pakistan). The song, named 'Aayi Aayi', is in Sindhi language and sung by four artists: Noma Ali Rajper, Babar Mangi (a hip-hop artist), Marvi, and Saiban. The song is written by Noman Ali Rajper, and the rapping part is written by Babar Mangi. The whole song, except for the rap part, tells the story of Umar-Marvi. Marvi is a girl from a small village, renowned for her beauty. One day, while fetching water from the well with her friends, a king named Umar Soomro appears with his crew and sees Marvi. He stops and asks for a glass of water. Marvi kindly gives him water, and King Umar holds her hand and kidnaps her. He locks her up in Umerkot, Sindh, and asks her to marry him. Marvi refuses and insists on returning to her home and people. Every day, King Umar asks her to marry him and become his queen, but Marvi consistently refuses. One day, she falls very ill. When the king comes and asks her to marry him as usual, she doesn't refuse but instead says that if she dies in this situation, thinking of her people and her country, then please bury her body in her homeland, Malhir, among her people. After hearing this, the king releases her from prison after one year. When she returns to her village in a very weakened state, her people see her coming back and start welcoming her by saying 'Aayi, Aayi, Aayi', which means 'she has come'. 'Aayi' means 'she comes'. OZAIR EDITZ, subscribe on YouTube."
